<!-- How It Works -->
<section class="section how-it-works" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>How It <span class="text-gradient">Works</span></h2>
      <p>Mutation testing injects bugs into your code to verify your tests catch them.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Parse Your Code</h3>
          <p>
            dart_mutant scans your <code>lib/</code> directory and builds an AST for each Dart file
            using tree-sitter. Generated files (<code>*.g.dart</code>, <code>*.freezed.dart</code>)
            are automatically excluded.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Generate Mutations</h3>
          <p>
            The AST is walked to find mutation candidates: arithmetic operators, comparisons,
            boolean literals, null-safety operators, and more. Each mutation is a small, targeted
            change.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Run Tests</h3>
          <p>
            For each mutation, dart_mutant modifies the source, runs <code>dart test</code>, and
            checks if any test fails. Mutations are tested in parallel for speed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-number">4</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Report Results</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Killed</strong> mutations = your tests caught the bug.
            <strong>Survived</strong> mutations = your tests missed it. The mutation score shows
            your true test effectiveness.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

